import useStyles from './SidebarStyles';
import {List, ListItem, ListItemIcon, ListItemText,Paper, Typography} from '@material-ui/core'
import FolderIcon from '@material-ui/icons/Folder'

import { NavLink } from 'react-router-dom';


const Sidebar = () => {

    const classes = useStyles();

    return (
        <Paper className={classes.sidebar}>
            <Typography variant="h5" className={classes.mainTitle}>Dashboard</Typography>
            <hr />
            <List component="ul" aria-label="main mailbox folders">

                <ListItem button component={NavLink} to="/client" activeClassName="Mui-selected">
                    <ListItemIcon>
                        <FolderIcon />
                    </ListItemIcon>
                    <ListItemText primary="Client" />
                    {/* <NavLink to='/client' activeStyle={{ color: 'green' }} activeClassName="active">Client</NavLink> */}
                </ListItem>
                <ListItem button component={NavLink} to="/branch" activeClassName="Mui-selected">
                    <ListItemIcon>
                        <FolderIcon />
                    </ListItemIcon>
                    <ListItemText primary="Branch" />
                </ListItem>
                <ListItem button component={NavLink} to="/contactperson" activeClassName="Mui-selected" >
                    <ListItemIcon>
                        <FolderIcon />
                    </ListItemIcon>
                    <ListItemText primary="Contact Person" />
                </ListItem>
                <ListItem button component={NavLink} to="/contract" activeClassName="Mui-selected" >
                    <ListItemIcon>
                        <FolderIcon />
                    </ListItemIcon>
                    <ListItemText primary="Contract" />
                </ListItem>

            </List>
        </Paper>
    )
}

export default Sidebar
